PROGRAM:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class printstatement {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println("Enter a number: ");
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int num = sc.nextInt();
        if(num%2==0 && num%4==0){
            System.out.println("Good morning");
        }
        else if(num%2==0){
            System.out.println("Good Afternoon");
        }
        else if(num%4==0){
            System.out.println("Good Evening");
        }
        else{
            System.out.println("Good Night");
        }
        sc.close();
        }
        }


OUTPUT:
Enter a number: 
8
Good morning
Enter a number: 
6
Good Afternoon
Enter a number: 
3
Good Night


DESCRIPTION:
This is program which prints the statement according to the conditions if the number is divided by both 2 and 3 it prints the statement "Good Morning".
else if if the number is only divided by 2 then it prints the statement "Good Afternoon" or if the number is only divided by 4 then it prints the statement "Good Evening".
else it prints "Good Night".
